tweet: The virus has begun to put all of that at risk. It is of paramount importance that we take steps to reverse the learning loss that has taken place and prevent any further erosion of our progress.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: In addition to presenting a public health crisis and disrupting our economy, the coronavirus also created enormous obstacles for our parents, teachers and students. Tennessee has made tremendous improvements in education over the last decade.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: Due to system outages from the explosion in downtown Nashville, @CSexton25 and I are advising #tnleg staff not to report to the Cordell Hull Building on Monday.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: An incredibly despicable act of destruction. My thoughts and prayers are with the people of downtown Nashville. I am grateful for the first responders who rushed into the chaos. And godspeed to those in law enforcement presently on the hunt for the evil doers.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: Merry Christmas and a happy new year to all!   ”These things I have spoken to you, so that in Me you may have peace. In the world you have tribulation, but take courage; I have overcome the world.” (John 16:33)

name: Randy McNally
tweet: May Christ’s peace and hope be with you and those you love today and throughout the new year. It is my hope that, despite the troubles behind us and ahead of us, every man, woman and child in Tennessee will rejoice in the promise, the gift and the miracle of Christmas.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: This year has had its challenges. But the Christmas season and the new year bring a promise of hope and renewal. During this time of peace and joy, whether you are together physically or virtually, I would like to wish the very best for you and your family.  https://t.co/jJImDAmdKv

name: Randy McNally
tweet: I am fully supportive of the directives @GovBillLee issued tonight. The actions he is taking are measured, thoughtful and absolutely necessary. I support him fully and I appreciate his leadership.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: Covid-19 deaths are surging and many hospitals are at or near capacity. The introduction of a vaccine is great news for the future but it will do nothing to prevent or manage this surge. Without a change in behavior, our health care system will be stretched to the breaking point.

name: Randy McNally

name: Randy McNally
tweet: Tennessee's strong fiscal position is due in large part to his work. Tennessee could not have asked for a better money cop. While this may be the end of his tenure as @TNCOT, I know he will continue to serve our state in different ways. He always has — and he always will.

name: Randy McNally
tweet: Justin Wilson is a giant in Tennessee state government. His service to our state has been unparalleled. Whether it was as Deputy Governor, Commissioner of Environment and Conservation, or as our beloved Comptroller, Justin has always put the interests of Tennessee over his own.
